# Assignment 2 – EC2 Deployment with Cloud-Init

## Objective
Deploy an EC2 instance on AWS using Terraform and automate its configuration
using a cloud-init YAML file. The instance should come online fully configured
with no manual intervention.

## Architecture Overview
- AWS EC2 instance (Amazon Linux)
- Security Group allowing HTTP (80) and SSH (22)
- Cloud-init YAML file used to install and configure Apache
- Public endpoint exposed via the EC2 public IP

## Terraform Files
- main.tf – Provider configuration, EC2 instance, security group, and user data
- variables.tf – Input variables
- outputs.tf – Public IP and URL of the EC2 instance
- cloud-init.yaml – Cloud-init configuration for Apache setup

## How It Works
1. Terraform provisions an EC2 instance in the default VPC
2. A security group allows inbound web traffic on port 80
3. Cloud-init runs on first boot to:
   - Install httpd
   - Create a simple HTML page
   - Enable and start the httpd service
4. The web server is immediately accessible via the public IP

## Deployment Steps
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply

